page.title: 07FLORA and FAUNA
page.content: In an area so exposed and so intensively farmed there is not much room for wildlife although there is a certain amount of "overflow" from the Wildfowl Trust. The almost complete lack of woodland - there are one or two very small clumps of trees - means that the sort of habitat which would support mammalian wildlife hardly exists. In addition, local farmers have done their best to make sure that anything whose interests conclict with those of the cattle and crops is dealt with. The few country lanes support a limited number of wild plants but these are all of a common nature. There are one or two interesting waterside plants to found along the banks of the River Cam.
